5:
Oooh! Al, look at my nails! Pretty,
right?
14:
Amelia painted it for us. We match.
Look at the sparkles.
19:
Your sense of color isn't bad, as
expected. I like this shade of indigo
blue in particular.
22:
What if we mixed it with the top coat
from the other day? It would look
good next to some gold.
28:
Oh, YES! That's super cute! Great
idea, Annie!
32:
You guys are getting along pretty
well. Weren't you wearing matching
accessories earlier this week?
37:
...I was asking about the town when
she came up and insisted that I
wear it.
44:
Speaking of which, that means
you're pretty interested in learning
more about people, right?
49:
...Can't I? I do what I want, and that's
what I want to do.
53:
Why not just experience Palpebra
for yourself? We can all go on a
shopping spree together!
60:
Showing myself in the mortal world
is asking for trouble.
63:
I'm not interested in causing a
scene. I detest screaming humans.
68:
I dunno if everyone's gonna be THAT
afraid to see you. We've already got
a dragon running around doing
jobs, after all.
72: Don't lump me in with that lowlife.
76:
Well, if you're that interested... We
can probably still take you and also
keep you out of the town itself.
80:
I've gotten a manicure in that place
before! They had so many choices, I
had the worst time picking out what
I wanted!
84:
I recommend that cafe. Their
pancakes are sweet and fluffy.
88:
The daily sales in that grocery turn it
into a warzone! Seriously, the prices
drops so low it's almost like buying
straight from the source...
92:
All right, slow down. I can't look in
every direction at once!
98:
And that's it for our flying tour of
Palpebra! Whew, being a guide is
more fun than I thought it'd be.
102:
We need to plan for another tour.
We didn't get to cover everything
today.
105:
Surely you don't intend on giving an
introduction for every building here...
108:
...I suppose I don't mind, as long as it
holds my interest.
112:
Are you curious about the
Kaleidoscope?
117:
...Not really. I was just taking in the
sights—how prosperous this place is
compared to other towns.
120:
I've visited various places since
coming to this world... But never one
like this.
125:
Ohhh, you just flew around, seeing
the world? That sounds awesome!
132:
I have learned firsthand the
pleasures of freedom, going
wherever I wish and doing whatever
I want.
135:
Ancient dragons originally existed to
serve as fodder for champions.
138:
I never believed I would one day be
free of that fate...
141:
No matter what you do to earn my
favor, I will not bend to your whims
and offer my assistance.
144:
I live the way I want... Besides, it
would be a waste to damage these
newly done nails.
149:
Don't worry, we get it. We're just
doing what we please, too.
152:
But it's nice when our interests align,
right? Just like today.
157: Yeah, I also live life on my own terms!
159:
Maybe I should look for a way to
grow wings sometime. If I figure out
how, I'll share the secret with you
and Stellie!
170:
Just growing wings doesn't sound
bad... as long as there aren't any
other side effects...
180:
Good evening, Anbach. Are you
unable to sleep?
184:
Yes. I find myself thinking about
matters best left alone.
191:
You were staring at it a lot today.
Are you certain you didn't want to
visit it?
195:
I must admit, I was curious about
the town as a whole, but...
198:
Stella, where do you think dragons,
ancient dragons, and serpents
come from?
201:
Ancient dragons are trapped in a
never-ending cycle of rebirth,
unable to have children like other
dragons...
204:
So where did we originally come
from?
208:
Your origins... Does it have
something to do with the
Kaleidoscope.
218:
Haha... It has been a while, An. I see
you are as clingy as always.
223:
Can you blame me? I haven't seen
you in so long...
226:
There's so much I want to share with
you—the things I've seen in the
world, hair accessories that would
look good on you...
230:
...There have been a lot of curious
dragons, lately. Searching for their
place of origin.
234:
...Not a single one of them have
been able to reclaim their sense of
self.
237: They are doomed to be forever lost...
241:
Yet here we stand, witness to the
same sights alongside these
children.
249:
The hour grows late. We should rest
together tonight. Will you join us,
Stella?
263:
I would... like to sleep beside you
tonight as well.
